::{{DIcon|Talk}} What does the museum do?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_501190124-->
:::'''Uldan:''' Belobog History and Culture Museum... As the name might suggest, it is a display gallery to showcase Belobog's history and culture to the public.
:::'''Uldan:''' After the Supreme Guardian Cocolia's sacrifice, her daughter, Bronya had decided to open seven hundred years' worth of the Everwinter City's history to the masses, so this museum has become a window to our past.
:::'''Uldan:''' Though, Belobog's history is only seven hundred years old, it's not really that long. Furthermore, many historical relics have already been buried under the snow, so the museum doesn't really have that many things to put up...
:::'''Uldan:''' ...But we still squeezed all we can in an attempt to string our story together with the little historical sources and art pieces we have. As for our current situation... I guess our goal is somewhat fulfilled.
::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Talk}} Belobog College of Art?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_501190129-->
:::'''Uldan:''' It is one of the colleges under the University of Belobog. It specializes in providing art education to its students, so that we can nurture more artistic talents for our city.
:::'''Uldan:''' The college is my alma mater, and I poured my heart and soul in it. I don't mean to indulge in self-praise, but when I was serving as its dean, the college's education level was at its historic peak...
:::'''Uldan:''' ...Ahem, A good man does not brag about the past, let us move on from this. The more important thing right now is our Belobog History and Culture Museum.
::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Talk}} I want to understand your past...
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_501190133-->
:::'''Uldan:''' Hehe, you're interested in an old man's past? I'm just an ordinary person, but since you asked, I'll tell you a little bit about myself.
:::'''Uldan:''' I was a graduate of the Belobog College of Art. Back then, I had no fear and naively believed that me and my art has the power to change the world...
:::'''Uldan:''' Well, you can guess the rest... Everywhere I go, I faced rejection. I became the stereotypical image of an artist... No opportunities, poor, starving, all of those. I could barely handle basic necessities like food and shelter, let alone my dreams.
:::'''Uldan:''' The funny thing is, when I was ready to set down my paint brush and stop doing art for good, but then my alma mater handed me a deal &mdash; they wanted me to go back and become a professor, and so I agreed.
:::'''Uldan:''' I gave it all I had, and eventually, I climbed my way up to become the dean of the college. I'm proud of all my students &mdash; many of which are famous artists in the Everwinter City.
:::'''Uldan:''' My life has been pretty smooth sailing ever since. After my retirement, I accepted Supreme Guardian Bronya's invitation and became the curator of this museum.
:::'''Uldan:''' What happens next? Well, we'll see.
::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Exit}} I have no further questions.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_501190141-->
:::'''Uldan:''' Heheh, take care now. I hope you enjoy this historical cultural tour.
:::<!--Ends the current performance-->
